  "id": "019ce533-ca9a-7b31-acf2-dbb9d6c4996c",
  "content": "# Parallel Agent Development Plan (2026-03-13)\n\n## Setup\nTwo Claude Code agents working in parallel on dashboard features, using git worktrees from master.\n\n### Agent A: Interactive Knowledge Graph\n- **Worktree:** `/workspaces/corvia-graph/` (branch: `feature/knowledge-graph`)\n- **Goal:** Replace flat edge table with force-directed canvas visualization\n- **Dev server:** port 8023\n- **Files:** `GraphView.tsx` (rewrite), `dashboard/mod.rs` (add scope endpoint), `api.ts`, `types.ts`\n\n### Agent B: Temporal History Explorer\n- **Worktree:** `/workspaces/corvia-history/` (branch: `feature/temporal-history`)\n- **Goal:** New History tab with supersession timeline, diff view, time travel slider\n- **Dev server:** port 8024\n- **Files:** `HistoryView.tsx` (new), `Layout.tsx` (add tab), `dashboard/mod.rs` (add history endpoints), `api.ts`, `types.ts`\n\n## Shared Files (merge points)\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-server/src/dashboard/mod.rs` — both add new routes + handlers (additive, trivial merge)\n- `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/api.ts` — both add new API functions (additive)\n- `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/types.ts` — both add new types (additive)\n\n## Merge Strategy\n1. Whichever agent finishes first merges to master\n2. Second agent rebases onto updated master\n3. Resolve any conflicts in shared files (all additive, should be trivial)\n4. Both agents share the same corvia server at localhost:8020 for knowledge coordination\n\n## Constraints\n- Neither agent touches `traits.rs` (kernel trait definitions)\n- Agent A: do not touch `Layout.tsx` or `HistoryView.tsx`\n- Agent B: do not touch `GraphView.tsx`",
